  "prompt": "Why isn\u2019t Pok\u00e9mon GO working?",
  "response": "There could be various reasons why Pok\u00e9mon GO is not working for you. Here are some common issues and solutions you can try:\n\n1. **Server Issues**: Sometimes the game's servers are down for maintenance or experiencing high traffic. You can check the official Pok\u00e9mon GO Twitter account or community forums to see if there are any announcements regarding server outages.\n\n2. **Internet Connection**: Ensure you have a stable internet connection, whether via Wi-Fi or mobile data. You can test your connection by trying to load other apps or websites.\n\n3. **App Updates**: Make sure you have the latest version of Pok\u00e9mon GO installed. Check your device's app store for any available updates.\n\n4. **Device Compatibility**: Ensure your device meets the game's minimum requirements. Sometimes, newer updates may require a device with more recent hardware or software versions.\n\n5. **Location Settings**: Pok\u00e9mon GO requires location services to be enabled. Make sure your GPS is turned on and that you\u2019ve granted the app permission to access your location.\n\n6. **Clear Cache/Data**: On Android devices, you can try clearing the app cache or data. This can often resolve issues caused by corrupted files.\n\n7. **Restart the App**: Close the app completely and then restart it. This can help refresh the app and fix any temporary glitches.\n\n8. **Reboot Your Device**: Sometimes a simple restart of your device can resolve issues with apps and connectivity.\n\n9. **Check for Restrictions**: Make sure that you do not have any restrictions on your data usage or location services that could prevent the app from working correctly.\n\n10. **Contact Support**: If none of the above solutions work, you may want to contact Niantic's support for assistance.\n\nIf you provide more specific details about your issue, I can give you more tailored advice.",
